// =============================================================================
// core.architecture.anti_patterns — ATS-V kernel-discharged anti-pattern bridges
// =============================================================================
//
// **Kernel-discharge attestation surface for the ATS-V architectural
// type system.**
//
// Mirrors the discharge pattern of `core.verify.codegen_soundness`
// and `core.verify.separation_soundness`: each axiom records a
// kernel-discharge bridge for an architectural invariant —
// admitted with explicit citation to the underlying refinement
// predicate, dispatched through a stable kernel intrinsic.
//
// ## Stable error codes
//
// Every anti-pattern carries a stable RFC code `ATS-V-AP-NNN`.
// Codes never get re-used across versions; deprecation requires
// ≥2 minor versions of dual support.  Diagnostics surface the
// code so both human reviewers and agents can pattern-match
// (dual-audience contract).
//
// ## 39-pattern roster (full canonical catalog)
//
// **Capability / composition core (AP-001..010):**
//   AP-001 CapabilityEscalation     undeclared capability used
//   AP-002 CapabilityLeak           linear/affine capability escapes scope
//   AP-003 DependencyCycle          composes_with graph cyclic
//   AP-004 TierMixing               cross-tier call without bridge
//   AP-005 FoundationDrift          incompatible foundations composed
//   AP-006 RegisterMixing           register-machine state mixes domains
//   AP-007 TxStraddling             operation crosses transactional boundary
//   AP-008 ResourceStraddling       single resource accessed across boundary
//   AP-009 LifecycleRegression      higher-rank cog cites lower-rank one
//   AP-010 CveIncomplete            strict mode missing CVE axis
//
// **Boundary / lifecycle / capability extensions (AP-011..026):**
//   AP-011 AbsoluteBoundaryAttempt    stratum = LAbs (AFN-T α violation)
//   AP-012 InvariantViolation         declared boundary invariant fails
//   AP-013 DanglingMessageType        message type without wire encoding
//   AP-014 UnauthenticatedCrossing    Network boundary without AuthFirst
//   AP-015 DeterministicViolation     DST test depends on non-deterministic
//   AP-016 CapabilityDuplication      Linear capability used twice
//   AP-017 OrphanCapability           Relevant cap declared but unused
//   AP-018 MissingHandoff             composition cap missing from list
//   AP-019 FoundationDowngrade        strong foundation downgraded w/o bridge
//   AP-020 TimeBoundLeakage           TimeBound capability outlives TTL
//   AP-021 PersistenceMismatch        Persist declared for non-durable op
//   AP-022 CapabilityLaundering       multi-hop privilege escalation
//   AP-023 FoundationForgery          declared ≠ cited axioms
//   AP-024 TransitiveLifecycleRegression   multi-hop AP-009
//   AP-025 DeclarationDrift           declared ≠ inferred shape
//   AP-026 FoundationContentMismatch  body uses foreign-foundation construct
//
// **MTAC modal-temporal arms (AP-027..032):**
//   AP-027 TemporalInconsistency      invariant fails across time-points
//   AP-028 CounterfactualBrittleness  fragile under decision swap
//   AP-029 MissedAdjoint              refactoring without inverse
//   AP-030 UniversalPropertyViolation universal claim violated
//   AP-031 PhantomEvolution           unsatisfiable trigger
//   AP-032 YonedaInequivalentRefactor observer-functor changes
//
// **CVE articulation-hygiene band (AP-033..039):**
//   These operationalise the CVE-architecture spec primitives:
//   ExecutabilitySense (§2.3.0), CognitiveSubstrate (§1.5),
//   FormalAnchoring (§4.5), Purpose (§14.6), the [I]/[H]/[✗]
//   discipline of §3.5, and the L6 register prohibitions of §16.
//
//   AP-033 RetractedCitationUse       citing a [✗] Retracted artefact
//   AP-034 HypothesisWithoutMaturationPlan  [H] cog without @plan(...)
//   AP-035 InterpretationInMatureCorpus     [I] in mature/strict corpus
//   AP-036 ObserverImpersonation      observer role mismatches assertion
//                                     register (L6 register collision)
//   AP-037 BoundlessAudit             strict-mode audit invocation
//                                     against a Shape with no declared
//                                     Purpose (§14.6 termination)
//   AP-038 ImplicitSubstrate          [T] in strict mode without declared
//                                     CognitiveSubstrate (§1.5 self-disclosure)
//   AP-039 AnchoringOverextension     formal claim outside CHL domain
//                                     without declared FormalAnchoring (§4.5)
//
// ## Discharge through 8 base + 4 red-team + 7 CVE-AH kernel intrinsics
//
// * `kernel_arch_capability_discipline` — composes AP-001 + AP-002.
// * `kernel_arch_boundary_check` — invariants across boundaries.
// * `kernel_arch_composition_check` — composition algebra.
// * `kernel_arch_lifecycle_check` — AP-009 LifecycleRegression.
// * `kernel_arch_foundation_consistency` — AP-005 FoundationDrift.
// * `kernel_arch_anti_pattern_check` — generic dispatcher (39 patterns).
// * `kernel_arch_cve_closure` — AP-010 CveIncomplete.
// * `kernel_arch_soundness_v0` — composes the 7 above.
// * `kernel_arch_capability_ontology_check` — AT-1 attack closure.
// * `kernel_arch_yoneda_canonical_roster_complete` — AT-3 attack closure.
// * `kernel_arch_theorem_cve_required` — AT-2 attack closure.
// * `kernel_arch_consumes_format_check` — AT-5 attack closure.
// * `kernel_arch_retracted_citation_check`           — AP-033.
// * `kernel_arch_hypothesis_plan_check`              — AP-034.
// * `kernel_arch_interpretation_in_mature_check`     — AP-035.
// * `kernel_arch_observer_impersonation_check`       — AP-036.
// * `kernel_arch_boundless_audit_check`              — AP-037.
// * `kernel_arch_implicit_substrate_check`           — AP-038.
// * `kernel_arch_anchoring_overextension_check`      — AP-039.
// =============================================================================

module core.architecture.anti_patterns;

mount core.prelude.{Bool, Int, Maybe, List, Text};

// =============================================================================
// AntiPatternCode — stable RFC code, 39-pattern canonical roster
// =============================================================================

/// Stable RFC error code `ATS-V-AP-NNN` per spec §32.4.
/// Pattern-matchable by agents; documented on docs site.
///
/// **39 canonical variants**:
///   * AP-001..010 — capability/composition core
///   * AP-011..026 — boundary/lifecycle/capability ontology extensions
///   * AP-027..032 — MTAC modal-temporal arms
///   * AP-033..039 — CVE articulation-hygiene band (cve-architecture
///                    spec §1.5, §2.3.0, §3.5, §4.5, §14.6, §16)
///
/// **Stability**: codes never get re-used; removing a pattern
/// requires deprecation cycle ≥ 2 minor versions per spec §29.5.
/// Mirrors `verum_kernel::arch_anti_pattern::AntiPatternCode`.
public type AntiPatternCode is
    // ----- Capability / composition core (AP-001..010) -----
    | CapabilityEscalation
    | CapabilityLeak
    | DependencyCycle
    | TierMixing
    | FoundationDrift
    | RegisterMixing
    | TxStraddling
    | ResourceStraddling
    | LifecycleRegression
    | CveIncomplete
    // ----- Boundary / lifecycle / capability ontology (AP-011..026) -----
    | AbsoluteBoundaryAttempt
    | InvariantViolation
    | DanglingMessageType
    | UnauthenticatedCrossing
    | DeterministicViolation
    | CapabilityDuplication
    | OrphanCapability
    | MissingHandoff
    | FoundationDowngrade
    | TimeBoundLeakage
    | PersistenceMismatch
    | CapabilityLaundering
    | FoundationForgery
    | TransitiveLifecycleRegression
    | DeclarationDrift
    | FoundationContentMismatch
    // ----- MTAC modal-temporal (AP-027..032) -----
    | TemporalInconsistency
    | CounterfactualBrittleness
    | MissedAdjoint
    | UniversalPropertyViolation
    | PhantomEvolution
    | YonedaInequivalentRefactor
    // ----- CVE articulation-hygiene band (AP-033..039) -----
    | RetractedCitationUse
    | HypothesisWithoutMaturationPlan
    | InterpretationInMatureCorpus
    | ObserverImpersonation
    | BoundlessAudit
    | ImplicitSubstrate
    | AnchoringOverextension;

